7193848140217306411.desc: This slow cooker alfredo is dairy free but if youre not, just use heavy cream in place of coconut milk! #easydinner #easyrecipe #weeknightdinner #crockpot #slowcooker #lazygirldinner #thatmom #lazymom #dairyfree  Mix 1 lb uncooked cajun sausage, 3c chicken broth, 1/2 can coconut milk, 2T nutritional yeast, 1/2c shredded parmesan, 1T cajun seasoning, minced garlic and dried minced onion to taste in the crockpot. Cook on low for 4 hours. Set crockpot to high and add 3 cups of uncooked pasta. Cook for ~30 minutes. Dont overcook the pasta! Optional: for a thicker sauce, mix 1tsp of cornstarch with 2tsp of cold water and then add to the crockpot. 7191957156042837294.desc: 4 russet potatoes, cut into 1” pieces 1/2 diced sweet onion or dried onion 1 tbsp minced garlic 1 tbsp @countrycrock plant butter 1 tbsp oil 1/2 tsp paprika 1 tsp salt Pepper to taste 2 cans of chicken broth 1 can of coconut milk 1/2 cup nutritional yeast Optional: Liquid smoke Lemon juice Bacon bits 1. Melt butter in a pot with oil. Sauté onions until translucent. Add garlic and cook for one minute.  2. Add potatoes, paprika, salt, and pepper and sauté for a few minutes.  3. Add chicken broth, coconut milk, and nutritional yeast. Add 1 tsp liquid smoke (optional). Stir to combine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.  4. Add 1/2 tsp of lemon juice (optional but makes it taste cheesier). Serve as is or use an immersion blender to blend some of the potatoes to make it creamier.  5. Top with bacon bits 🤤  #dairyfree #dairyfreerecipes #easyrecipe #dinnerideas #momhacks #lazymomdinner #comfortfood  Vegan potato soup Dairy free potato soup recipe
